there is a large [INAUDIBLE]..

00:06:02.370 --> 00:06:06.150 align:middle line:84%
The aim of screening is not
to find these abnormalities.

00:06:06.150 --> 00:06:08.670 align:middle line:90%


00:06:08.670 --> 00:06:10.920 align:middle line:90%
>> Because big tumors are scary.

00:06:10.920 --> 00:06:12.300 align:middle line:90%
And for a good reason--

00:06:12.300 --> 00:06:15.810 align:middle line:84%
for a long time, breast
cancer was incurable.

00:06:15.810 --> 00:06:17.880 align:middle line:84%
It was the first
known cancer and is

00:06:17.880 --> 00:06:22.050 align:middle line:84%
extremely recognizable as
it eats away at the breast.

00:06:22.050 --> 00:06:24.870 align:middle line:90%
The tumor develops like a crab.

00:06:24.870 --> 00:06:29.790 align:middle line:84%
Indeed, this image gave
the disease its name.

00:06:29.790 --> 00:06:31.740 align:middle line:84%
For a long time,
the only treatment

00:06:31.740 --> 00:06:35.310 align:middle line:84%
was the removal of the
breast, a mastectomy.

00:06:35.310 --> 00:06:37.320 align:middle line:84%
In the 19th century,
people began

00:06:37.320 --> 00:06:41.100 align:middle line:84%
to believe that this operation
was more effective with smaller

00:06:41.100 --> 00:06:42.480 align:middle line:90%
tumors.

00:06:42.480 --> 00:06:44.250 align:middle line:84%
The survival of the
patient, therefore,

00:06:44.250 --> 00:06:47.040 align:middle line:84%
depends on the stage at when
they seek medical advice.

00:06:47.040 --> 00:06:51.822 align:middle line:90%


00:06:51.822 --> 00:06:56.250 align:middle line:84%
>> At least a third of those
who die of cancer could be saved

00:06:56.250 --> 00:06:58.230 align:middle line:84%
if they started
treatment early enough.

00:06:58.230 --> 00:07:00.080 align:middle line:90%


00:07:00.080 --> 00:07:02.840 align:middle line:84%
>> After the Second World
War, campaigns were launched

00:07:02.840 --> 00:07:06.080 align:middle line:84%
to encourage women to seek
medical advice as soon as they

00:07:06.080 --> 00:07:08.270 align:middle line:90%
discovered the first symptoms.

00:07:08.270 --> 00:07:12.360 align:middle line:84%
Cancer was an enemy
that had to be beaten.

00:07:12.360 --> 00:07:15.960 align:middle line:84%
And a new weapon was now part
of the struggle, radiography,

00:07:15.960 --> 00:07:20.460 align:middle line:84%
helping detect cancer even
before a tumor could be felt.

00:07:20.460 --> 00:07:23.340 align:middle line:84%
The idea then emerged
of offering all women

00:07:23.340 --> 00:07:26.820 align:middle line:84%
regular mammograms,
however healthy they were.

00:07:26.820 --> 00:07:29.340 align:middle line:84%
That would bring
down mortality rates.

00:07:29.340 --> 00:07:31.500 align:middle line:84%
And to prove it, a
series of experiments

00:07:31.500 --> 00:07:37.630 align:middle line:90%
was carried out in the 1970s.

00:07:37.630 --> 00:07:40.675 align:middle line:84%
Hundreds of thousands of women
were divided into two groups.

00:07:40.675 --> 00:07:44.430 align:middle line:90%


00:07:44.430 --> 00:07:47.930 align:middle line:84%
The first group was invited to
undergo a clinical examination

00:07:47.930 --> 00:07:51.890 align:middle line:90%
and mammogram every year.

00:07:51.890 --> 00:07:55.514 align:middle line:84%
The second group simply
carried on with their lives.

00:07:55.514 --> 00:08:02.680 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:08:02.680 --> 00:08:05.180 align:middle line:90%
The experiment lasted 10 years.

00:08:05.180 --> 00:08:07.270 align:middle line:84%
And at the end, they
looked at incidences

00:08:07.270 --> 00:08:10.655 align:middle line:84%
of breast cancer in the two
groups and the number of deaths

00:08:10.655 --> 00:08:11.455 align:middle line:90%
from breast cancer.

00:08:11.455 --> 00:08:15.290 align:middle line:90%


00:08:15.290 --> 00:08:17.560 align:middle line:84%
In the group that did
not undergo screening,

00:08:17.560 --> 00:08:21.160 align:middle line:90%
there were 30% more deaths.

00:08:21.160 --> 00:08:22.840 align:middle line:90%
A conclusion was reached.

00:08:22.840 --> 00:08:25.840 align:middle line:84%
The experiments proved
what people had suspected.

00:08:25.840 --> 00:08:30.430 align:middle line:84%
Breast cancer screening through
mammograms was a success.

00:08:30.430 --> 00:08:32.469 align:middle line:84%
It became part of
public health policy.

00:08:32.469 --> 00:08:38.559 align:middle line:90%


00:08:38.559 --> 00:08:40.960 align:middle line:84%
All over the world,
every two years,

00:08:40.960 --> 00:08:45.340 align:middle line:84%
women aged between 50 and
74 with no apparent symptoms

00:08:45.340 --> 00:08:48.550 align:middle line:84%
receive an invitation to
undergo a free examination

00:08:48.550 --> 00:08:52.660 align:middle line:84%
and mammogram at a state
certified medical facility.

00:08:52.660 --> 00:08:55.720 align:middle line:84%
Some gynecologists even
take it into their own hands

00:08:55.720 --> 00:08:58.525 align:middle line:84%
to offer these checks to
women from the age of 40.

00:08:58.525 --> 00:09:01.480 align:middle line:90%


00:09:01.480 --> 00:09:02.380 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

