It was like a tidal
wave inside me.

00:10:41.950 --> 00:10:44.080 align:middle line:90%
I was trembling.

00:10:44.080 --> 00:10:49.150 align:middle line:84%
I had to try to keep my calm
and not burst into tears.

00:10:49.150 --> 00:10:51.700 align:middle line:84%
Then the radiologist
reassured me,

00:10:51.700 --> 00:10:53.950 align:middle line:84%
saying I'd get
treatment very quickly.

00:10:53.950 --> 00:10:57.100 align:middle line:84%
And everything was
going to be OK.

00:10:57.100 --> 00:10:59.320 align:middle line:84%
That gave me back
some confidence.

00:10:59.320 --> 00:11:01.440 align:middle line:84%
And I went home
a little happier.

00:11:01.440 --> 00:11:10.300 align:middle line:90%


00:11:10.300 --> 00:11:11.855 align:middle line:84%
>> Monique has now
become a patient.

00:11:11.855 --> 00:11:18.820 align:middle line:90%


00:11:18.820 --> 00:11:20.380 align:middle line:84%
She has been given
an appointment

00:11:20.380 --> 00:11:22.780 align:middle line:84%
at the hospital in
Lille for a biopsy

00:11:22.780 --> 00:11:26.402 align:middle line:84%
to be carried out by radiologist
Luc [SPEAKING FRENCH]..

00:11:26.402 --> 00:11:27.305 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:11:27.305 --> 00:11:29.180 align:middle line:84%
>>INTERPRETER: So then
what we're going to do

00:11:29.180 --> 00:11:31.352 align:middle line:84%
is sit you down on
a table behind us.

00:11:31.352 --> 00:11:32.810 align:middle line:84%
And we'll set you
up so that we can

00:11:32.810 --> 00:11:35.780 align:middle line:84%
get a sample of those
little calcified elements

00:11:35.780 --> 00:11:37.460 align:middle line:90%
deep inside the breast.

00:11:37.460 --> 00:11:39.470 align:middle line:84%
All those little
dots are calcium.

00:11:39.470 --> 00:11:41.810 align:middle line:84%
You can only see them
with a mammogram.

00:11:41.810 --> 00:11:43.130 align:middle line:90%
You can't feel them.

00:11:43.130 --> 00:11:46.010 align:middle line:84%
You can't even see them
with the naked eye.

00:11:46.010 --> 00:11:48.870 align:middle line:84%
Right now, we don't
know what they are.

00:11:48.870 --> 00:11:51.500 align:middle line:84%
So our aim is to
extract enough of them

00:11:51.500 --> 00:11:54.650 align:middle line:84%
to find out if there are
cancerous or precancerous cells

00:11:54.650 --> 00:11:55.590 align:middle line:90%
there.

00:11:55.590 --> 00:11:56.900 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:11:56.900 --> 00:11:57.700 align:middle line:90%
>>INTERPRETER: OK.

00:11:57.700 --> 00:12:00.560 align:middle line:90%
Come and lie down on the table.

00:12:00.560 --> 00:12:04.760 align:middle line:84%
And place your breasts
through the hole.

00:12:04.760 --> 00:12:08.100 align:middle line:84%
>> Microcalcifications
don't make a solid tumor.

00:12:08.100 --> 00:12:10.310 align:middle line:84%
And to extract a
sample, the radiologist

00:12:10.310 --> 00:12:14.360 align:middle line:84%
has to perform a macrobiopsy
with a very wide needle that

00:12:14.360 --> 00:12:15.950 align:middle line:90%
will leave a bruise.

00:12:15.950 --> 00:12:18.764 align:middle line:90%
A local anesthetic is essential.

00:12:18.764 --> 00:12:20.290 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:12:20.290 --> 00:12:22.510 align:middle line:84%
>>INTERPRETER: Biopsies
are not a banal procedure.

00:12:22.510 --> 00:12:25.180 align:middle line:84%
It's an aggressive procedure,
whatever the outcome.

00:12:25.180 --> 00:12:27.916 align:middle line:90%


00:12:27.916 --> 00:12:29.230 align:middle line:90%
>> Ow, ow, ow, ah.

00:12:29.230 --> 00:12:30.880 align:middle line:90%
>>INTERPRETER: That hurts?

00:12:30.880 --> 00:12:34.980 align:middle line:84%
>> Some patients require
a little more anesthetic.

00:12:34.980 --> 00:12:36.910 align:middle line:84%
>>INTERPRETER: Is
your head spinning?

00:12:36.910 --> 00:12:38.160 align:middle line:90%
>>INTERPRETER: Can you see me?

00:12:38.160 --> 00:12:41.950 align:middle line:90%


00:12:41.950 --> 00:12:43.225 align:middle line:90%
>>INTERPRETER: Are you OK?

00:12:43.225 --> 00:12:44.350 align:middle line:90%
>>INTERPRETER: Hi, Monique.

00:12:44.350 --> 00:12:45.150 align:middle line:90%
How are you?

00:12:45.150 --> 00:12:47.210 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:12:47.210 --> 00:12:49.210 align:middle line:84%
>>INTERPRETER: She's not
doing well, poor thing.

00:12:49.210 --> 00:12:55.260 align:middle line:90%


00:12:55.260 --> 00:12:58.410 align:middle line:84%
>> Despite her fainting, they
must carry on with the biopsy

00:12:58.410 --> 00:13:02.685 align:middle line:84%
because that's the only
way to obtain a diagnosis.

00:13:02.685 --> 00:13:04.595 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:13:04.595 --> 00:13:05.470 align:middle line:90%
>>INTERPRETER: Great.

00:13:05.470 --> 00:13:06.080 align:middle line:90%
Don't worry.

00:13:06.080 --> 00:13:06.997 align:middle line:90%
Everything will be OK.

00:13:06.997 --> 00:13:11.650 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:13:11.650 --> 00:13:15.280 align:middle line:84%
>> Monique's lesions, detected
by chance during the screening,

00:13:15.280 --> 00:13:18.867 align:middle line:84%
are only a first
indication of a problem.

00:13:18.867 --> 00:13:19.700 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:13:19.700 --> 00:13:21.850 align:middle line:84%
>> You don't die of
cancer inside the breast.

00:13:21.850 --> 00:13:25.120 align:middle line:84%
You die of the metastases or
the cells that travel everywhere

00:13:25.120 --> 00:13:27.700 align:middle line:90%
else, creating metastases.

00:13:27.700 --> 00:13:30.940 align:middle line:84%
The idea is to detect
the smallest lesions

00:13:30.940 --> 00:13:34.330 align:middle line:84%
with the hope that
they never evolve

00:13:34.330 --> 00:13:36.880 align:middle line:84%
and that women don't
have to undergo

00:13:36.880 --> 00:13:38.810 align:middle line:84%
all those aggressive
treatments we all fear,

00:13:38.810 --> 00:13:40.630 align:middle line:90%
such as chemotherapy.

00:13:40.630 --> 00:13:45.070 align:middle line:84%
Our aim is to detect cancer
at an intermammary stage, when

00:13:45.070 --> 00:13:47.530 align:middle line:84%
it's still contained
in the breast.

00:13:47.530 --> 00:13:51.130 align:middle line:84%
In Monique's case, we're at the
best stage we could hope for.

00:13:51.130 --> 00:13:52.430 align:middle line:90%
She can't sense it.

00:13:52.430 --> 00:13:53.560 align:middle line:90%
We can't see it.

00:13:53.560 --> 00:13:55.480 align:middle line:84%
And you can't feel
it with her fingers.

00:13:55.480 --> 00:13:57.070 align:middle line:84%
If she had waited
to feel a lump,

00:13:57.070 --> 00:14:00.998 align:middle line:84%
we would probably be at a
later stage in her illness.

00:14:00.998 --> 00:14:03.393 align:middle line:90%
[MOOING]

00:14:03.393 --> 00:14:10.100 align:middle line:90%


00:14:10.100 --> 00:14:15.330 align:middle line:84%
>> For Monique and her family,
a long wait is just beginning.

00:14:15.330 --> 00:14:18.330 align:middle line:84%
Despite shopping trips with
her girlfriends and attempts

00:14:18.330 --> 00:14:20.354 align:middle line:90%
at distraction--

00:14:20.354 --> 00:14:21.330 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:14:21.330 --> 00:14:24.290 align:middle line:84%
>>INTERPRETER: This place should
be covered by health insurance.

00:14:24.290 --> 00:14:26.670 align:middle line:84%
>>INTERPRETER: Well,
that's not a bad idea.

00:14:26.670 --> 00:14:27.780 align:middle line:90%
I'll make your request.

00:14:27.780 --> 00:14:31.300 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:14:31.300 --> 00:14:34.320 align:middle line:84%
>> The idea of being sick
has gained the upper hand.

00:14:34.320 --> 00:14:37.680 align:middle line:84%
The fear of cancer has brutally
invaded her daily life.

00:14:37.680 --> 00:14:46.660 align:middle line:90%


00:14:46.660 --> 00:14:47.500 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:14:47.500 --> 00:14:51.600 align:middle line:84%
>>INTERPRETER: I'm scared
of death, of losing my wife.

00:14:51.600 --> 00:14:54.670 align:middle line:84%
We're waiting for
results of the biopsy.

00:14:54.670 --> 00:14:56.280 align:middle line:84%
So the hardest thing
is yet to come.

00:14:56.280 --> 00:14:59.100 align:middle line:90%


00:14:59.100 --> 00:15:01.960 align:middle line:90%
We know people die of this.

00:15:01.960 --> 00:15:02.760 align:middle line:90%
It's a big deal.

00:15:02.760 --> 00:15:08.117 align:middle line:90%


00:15:08.117 --> 00:15:08.950 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:15:08.950 --> 00:15:12.880 align:middle line:84%
>>INTERPRETER: You never
know where it's going to go.

00:15:12.880 --> 00:15:16.720 align:middle line:84%
My sister had a cancer
at a very advanced stage.

00:15:16.720 --> 00:15:18.770 align:middle line:90%
So I really know this process.

00:15:18.770 --> 00:15:21.100 align:middle line:84%
And that's what
really frightens me.

00:15:21.100 --> 00:15:24.850 align:middle line:90%


00:15:24.850 --> 00:15:31.460 align:middle line:84%
There's the physical
degradation, the weight loss,

00:15:31.460 --> 00:15:35.835 align:middle line:84%
hair loss, and all the
medication protocol.

00:15:35.835 --> 00:15:39.140 align:middle line:90%


00:15:39.140 --> 00:15:42.860 align:middle line:84%
It tires you out and
destroys you from within.

00:15:42.860 --> 00:15:52.130 align:middle line:90%


00:15:52.130 --> 00:15:54.770 align:middle line:84%
>> The uncertainty
continues for two weeks,

00:15:54.770 --> 00:15:57.500 align:middle line:84%
the time it takes for the
samples to be analyzed under

00:15:57.500 --> 00:16:00.920 align:middle line:84%
a microscope in an anatomical
pathology laboratory.

00:16:00.920 --> 00:16:03.520 align:middle line:90%


00:16:03.520 --> 00:16:05.510 align:middle line:84%
[SPEAKING FRENCH]
is a pathologist

00:16:05.510 --> 00:16:08.300 align:middle line:84%
and a specialist who is little
known to the general public.

00:16:08.300 --> 00:16:11.880 align:middle line:90%


00:16:11.880 --> 00:16:12.830 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:16:12.830 --> 00:16:15.560 align:middle line:84%
>>INTERPRETER: We're the ones
who make the cancer diagnosis.

00:16:15.560 --> 00:16:17.900 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not saying
this to show off.

00:16:17.900 --> 00:16:21.200 align:middle line:84%
We diagnose by looking at the
lesions under the microscope.

00:16:21.200 --> 00:16:24.866 align:middle line:90%


00:16:24.866 --> 00:16:27.910 align:middle line:84%
And depending on how the cell
looks, if they look good,

00:16:27.910 --> 00:16:29.320 align:middle line:90%
they're benign cells.

00:16:29.320 --> 00:16:31.540 align:middle line:84%
And if they look bad,
they are malignant.

00:16:31.540 --> 00:16:34.690 align:middle line:90%


00:16:34.690 --> 00:16:37.780 align:middle line:84%
>> Not all biopsies from breast
cancer screening turn out to be

00:16:37.780 --> 00:16:40.090 align:middle line:84%
cancerous under the
doctor's microscope.

00:16:40.090 --> 00:16:42.517 align:middle line:90%


00:16:42.517 --> 00:16:43.350 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:16:43.350 --> 00:16:45.300 align:middle line:84%
>>INTERPRETER: Out
of 100 biopsies,

00:16:45.300 --> 00:16:49.450 align:middle line:84%
only 10 are real cancers
or invasive cancers.

00:16:49.450 --> 00:16:50.580 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:16:50.580 --> 00:16:53.790 align:middle line:84%
>>INTERPRETER: They're
easy to diagnose.

00:16:53.790 --> 00:16:58.020 align:middle line:84%
And then we'll find 10
precancerous lesions.

00:16:58.020 --> 00:16:59.640 align:middle line:90%
>> Precancerous lesions?

00:16:59.640 --> 00:17:01.980 align:middle line:84%
Here the pathologist
comes up against a problem

00:17:01.980 --> 00:17:03.746 align:middle line:90%
to do with terminology.

00:17:03.746 --> 00:17:05.410 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:17:05.410 --> 00:17:08.770 align:middle line:84%
>>INTERPRETER: With colon
cancer, we call them edemas.

00:17:08.770 --> 00:17:10.967 align:middle line:84%
>> That's a reassuring
word for a benign tumor.

00:17:10.967 --> 00:17:11.800 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:17:11.800 --> 00:17:13.300 align:middle line:84%
>>INTERPRETER:
With breast cancer,

00:17:13.300 --> 00:17:17.440 align:middle line:84%
precancerous lesions are
called carcinoma in situ.

00:17:17.440 --> 00:17:20.230 align:middle line:84%
The word carcinoma
in situ naturally

00:17:20.230 --> 00:17:22.480 align:middle line:84%
worries both
patients and doctors

00:17:22.480 --> 00:17:24.040 align:middle line:90%
who then think it's cancer.

00:17:24.040 --> 00:17:25.510 align:middle line:90%
But it's not cancer.

00:17:25.510 --> 00:17:27.910 align:middle line:84%
It's a precancerous
lesion that brings

00:17:27.910 --> 00:17:30.710 align:middle line:90%
an increased risk of cancer.

00:17:30.710 --> 00:17:33.060 align:middle line:84%
But it won't necessarily
become cancer.

00:17:33.060 --> 00:17:39.220 align:middle line:84%
And this is still very confusing
for both doctors and patients.

00:17:39.220 --> 00:17:41.555 align:middle line:84%
>> Today, we treat these
cancer risks like full-fledged

00:17:41.555 --> 00:17:42.355 align:middle line:90%
cancers.

00:17:42.355 --> 00:17:48.270 align:middle line:90%


00:17:48.270 --> 00:17:50.080 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:17:50.080 --> 00:17:52.680 align:middle line:84%
>>INTERPRETER: If you say it's
benign, the patient goes home.

00:17:52.680 --> 00:17:56.310 align:middle line:84%
If you say it's carcinoma,
carcinoma in situ,

00:17:56.310 --> 00:17:59.700 align:middle line:84%
they risk having
to undergo surgery.

00:17:59.700 --> 00:18:02.970 align:middle line:84%
It's something I think about,
and it makes me uncomfortable.

00:18:02.970 --> 00:18:04.800 align:middle line:84%
I'm uncomfortable
about screening.

00:18:04.800 --> 00:18:06.060 align:middle line:90%
And I'd like it to stop.

00:18:06.060 --> 00:18:13.090 align:middle line:90%


00:18:13.090 --> 00:18:16.270 align:middle line:84%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH] is one of
the only pathologists to share

00:18:16.270 --> 00:18:17.620 align:middle line:90%
his doubts.

00:18:17.620 --> 00:18:20.410 align:middle line:84%
Within the framework of
breast cancer screening,

00:18:20.410 --> 00:18:23.290 align:middle line:84%
the diagnosis is based on
an ambiguous definition

00:18:23.290 --> 00:18:25.300 align:middle line:90%
of the disease.

00:18:25.300 --> 00:18:28.000 align:middle line:84%
Yet calling precancerous
lesions cancer

00:18:28.000 --> 00:18:31.960 align:middle line:84%
has immediate
consequences for women.

00:18:31.960 --> 00:18:35.320 align:middle line:84%
Despite being in good health,
they are classified as sick

00:18:35.320 --> 00:18:39.130 align:middle line:84%
and their world becomes one
of hospitals, medication,

00:18:39.130 --> 00:18:41.650 align:middle line:90%
and aggressive therapies.

00:18:41.650 --> 00:18:44.830 align:middle line:84%
60% of cancer patients
experience a loss

00:18:44.830 --> 00:18:47.110 align:middle line:90%
of revenue and stop working.

00:18:47.110 --> 00:18:51.130 align:middle line:84%
Obtaining loan insurance
becomes an uphill battle.

00:18:51.130 --> 00:18:54.660 align:middle line:84%
This anxiety lasts
for a long time.

00:18:54.660 --> 00:18:58.462 align:middle line:84%
25% of patients
become depressed.

00:18:58.462 --> 00:19:02.840 align:middle line:90%
[STREET NOISE]

00:19:02.840 --> 00:19:04.160 align:middle line:90%
Two weeks have passed.

00:19:04.160 --> 00:19:05.900 align:middle line:84%
And Monique returns
to the hospital

00:19:05.900 --> 00:19:07.610 align:middle line:84%
to get the results
from her biopsy.

00:19:07.610 --> 00:19:12.570 align:middle line:90%


00:19:12.570 --> 00:19:13.700 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:19:13.700 --> 00:19:15.200 align:middle line:84%
>>INTERPRETER: I've
got the results.

00:19:15.200 --> 00:19:17.480 align:middle line:84%
And cancerous cells
have been detected.

00:19:17.480 --> 00:19:18.930 align:middle line:90%
It's breast cancer.

00:19:18.930 --> 00:19:23.030 align:middle line:84%
And here at the center, we
consider these precancerous.

00:19:23.030 --> 00:19:25.570 align:middle line:84%
At this stage, it's
what we call in situ.

00:19:25.570 --> 00:19:28.100 align:middle line:90%
It is confined inside the ducts.

00:19:28.100 --> 00:19:30.170 align:middle line:84%
It hasn't come out
of the ducts, and it

00:19:30.170 --> 00:19:34.040 align:middle line:84%
hasn't entered the lymph nodes
and hasn't gone elsewhere.

00:19:34.040 --> 00:19:36.800 align:middle line:84%
That means it's only
local in the breast.

00:19:36.800 --> 00:19:39.410 align:middle line:84%
Then we have to go through
all the various stages.

00:19:39.410 --> 00:19:41.060 align:middle line:90%
And that will be tough.

00:19:41.060 --> 00:19:43.116 align:middle line:90%
It's quite serious.

00:19:43.116 --> 00:19:44.050 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:19:44.050 --> 00:19:44.967 align:middle line:90%
>>INTERPRETER: I know.

00:19:44.967 --> 00:19:45.800 align:middle line:90%
I know all about it.

00:19:45.800 --> 00:19:47.467 align:middle line:84%
>>INTERPRETER: It's
not going to be what

00:19:47.467 --> 00:19:48.860 align:middle line:90%
like happened to your sister.

00:19:48.860 --> 00:19:51.100 align:middle line:84%
You've got the image
of your sister.

00:19:51.100 --> 00:19:53.250 align:middle line:90%
But you can't compare it.

00:19:53.250 --> 00:19:54.050 align:middle line:90%
>> [CRYING]

00:19:54.050 --> 00:19:55.092 align:middle line:90%
>>INTERPRETER: I'm sorry.

00:19:55.092 --> 00:20:07.480 align:middle line:90%


00:20:07.480 --> 00:20:08.802 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:20:08.802 --> 00:20:10.635 align:middle line:84%
>>INTERPRETER: We are
at a very early stage.

00:20:10.635 --> 00:20:13.620 align:middle line:90%


00:20:13.620 --> 00:20:16.290 align:middle line:84%
It's the best we
might have hoped for.

00:20:16.290 --> 00:20:17.470 align:middle line:90%
We need to treat you.

00:20:17.470 --> 00:20:19.790 align:middle line:84%
And in the end, we
hope to cure you

00:20:19.790 --> 00:20:22.100 align:middle line:90%
of a disease you don't have.

00:20:22.100 --> 00:20:26.510 align:middle line:84%
Right now you have abnormalities
that show up on an X-ray.

00:20:26.510 --> 00:20:27.760 align:middle line:90%
You're not ill.

00:20:27.760 --> 00:20:28.560 align:middle line:90%
You're healthy.

00:20:28.560 --> 00:20:37.300 align:middle line:90%


00:20:37.300 --> 00:20:39.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Cancer or precancer?

00:20:39.610 --> 00:20:42.820 align:middle line:84%
In the confusion, all Monique
hears is that she's got cancer.

00:20:42.820 --> 00:20:45.590 align:middle line:90%


00:20:45.590 --> 00:20:47.020 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:20:47.020 --> 00:20:51.170 align:middle line:84%
>>INTERPRETER: There is a before
and an after the diagnosis.

00:20:51.170 --> 00:20:53.620 align:middle line:84%
There's the before
the diagnosis,

00:20:53.620 --> 00:20:57.550 align:middle line:84%
when you have an ordinary
life with your daily routine.

00:20:57.550 --> 00:21:00.550 align:middle line:84%
And then after,
when you continue

00:21:00.550 --> 00:21:02.740 align:middle line:84%
with your daily life
with the knowledge

00:21:02.740 --> 00:21:05.710 align:middle line:90%
that you have a fatal disease.

00:21:05.710 --> 00:21:08.460 align:middle line:84%
So of course, it
changes everything.

00:21:08.460 --> 00:21:10.300 align:middle line:84%
You don't see
things the same way.

00:21:10.300 --> 00:21:15.590 align:middle line:90%


00:21:15.590 --> 00:21:17.590 align:middle line:84%
I want to spend all
the money I've saved.

00:21:17.590 --> 00:21:22.450 align:middle line:84%
Because I may be never going
to be able to enjoy it.

00:21:22.450 --> 00:21:24.210 align:middle line:90%
