00:27:56.530 --> 00:28:00.140 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:28:00.140 --> 00:28:02.140 align:middle line:84%
>>INTERPRETER: The principle
of cancer screening

00:28:02.140 --> 00:28:03.200 align:middle line:90%
is very simple.

00:28:03.200 --> 00:28:05.710 align:middle line:84%
You have to try and
detect presence of cancer

00:28:05.710 --> 00:28:07.255 align:middle line:90%
before it becomes advanced.

00:28:07.255 --> 00:28:10.840 align:middle line:90%


00:28:10.840 --> 00:28:13.720 align:middle line:84%
If breast cancer screening
is responsible for reduction

00:28:13.720 --> 00:28:18.640 align:middle line:84%
in death from breast
cancer in a population,

00:28:18.640 --> 00:28:20.620 align:middle line:84%
then we should be able
to see a reduction

00:28:20.620 --> 00:28:24.610 align:middle line:84%
in incidence of advanced breast
cancer in that same population.

00:28:24.610 --> 00:28:27.340 align:middle line:84%
That would be the only
proof of the efficiency

00:28:27.340 --> 00:28:28.490 align:middle line:90%
of cancer screening.

00:28:28.490 --> 00:28:33.880 align:middle line:90%


00:28:33.880 --> 00:28:35.950 align:middle line:84%
>> In the case of
uterine cancer,

00:28:35.950 --> 00:28:39.400 align:middle line:84%
the rate of advanced cases of
